data.chText: 国歌；（组织或群体的）社歌，团歌
data.enText: a song which has a special importance for a country, an organization, or a particular group of people and is sung on special occasions

data.chText: 欧洲颂歌在开幕式和闭幕式上演奏。
data.enText: The European anthem was played at the opening and closing ceremonies.

data.chText: （宗教）赞美歌（常由管风琴伴奏）
data.enText: a short religious song for a choir (= a group of singers), often with an organ

simple_means.memory_skill: anth 花 + em → 唱完圣歌遍地花开 → 圣歌

means: (宗教)赞美歌(常由管风琴伴奏)

tr: a song of praise (to God or to a saint or to a nation)
a song of devotion or loyalty (as to a nation or school)

value.def: An anthem is a song which is used to represent a particular nation, society, or group and which is sung on special occasions.

example.ex: The band played the Czech anthem.

value.tran: 国歌；（代表某一社会或团体的）颂歌，赞歌

partsOfSpeech.dec: anth 花 + em → 唱完圣歌遍地花开 → 圣歌
anth 花 + esis 生物学名词 → 开花期；开花
anth 花 + ology …学 → 像采花一样收集精品 → 选集
